Bauchi State House of Assembly candidate for Toro/Jama’a Constituency on the platform of New Nigeria Peoples Party (NNPP), Ibrahim Tilde, has facilitated the donation of N20 million to Jama’atul Izalatil Bid’ah Wa Iqamatussunnah (JIBWIS) Tilden Fulani Branch of Toro Local Council for the purchase of Eid Ground land and construction of school. While presenting the money to JIBWIS, yesterday, Tilde said, as part of his commitment to attract development to his constituency, he had solicited grants and interventions for his community from his business associates, and one of them made the donation. He explained that the donation was meant to help the group acquire a plot of land for permanent Eid Ground and complete its ongoing construction of Islamic school in the area.